public struct ImmutableArray<T>
{
	public class Builder
    {
+       public bool Remove(T element, IEqualityComparer<T> equalityComparer);
    }
}
```

`ImmutableArray<T>` itself [already exposes such a method](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.collections.immutable.immutablearray-1.remove?view=netcore-3.0#System_Collections_Immutable_ImmutableArray_1_Remove__0_System_Collections_Generic_IEqualityComparer__0__) and adding it to the builder doesn't seem like it would take much effort.

