Suggest adding an API that allows callers to determine the version of the Unicode Standard currently supported by the `CharUnicodeInfo` class.

```cs
namespace System.Globalization
{
    public static class CharUnicodeInfo
    {
        public static Version UnicodeVersion { get; }
    }
}
```

This will return a `System.Version` representing the Unicode data files which have been ingested to form the `CharUnicodeInfo` backing tables. As of this writing, the return value would be "11.0.0". Once we update the backing data, it'll read "12.1.0". And so on each time we ingest new data.

Per the versioning scheme listed at https://www.unicode.org/versions/#Version_Numbering, Unicode Standard version numbers are always in the format _\<major\>.\<minor\>.\<update\>_. So this makes the `System.Version` class ideal for representing such data.

