Imagine I need to unindent some raw JSON (for example, for error messages and logging). There is no simple way to do that; instead, I ended up writing the following, which seems a bit clunky:

```C#
public static string ChangeIndentation(string value, bool indented)
{
    using (var stream = new MemoryStream())
    {
        var options = new JsonWriterOptions { Indented = indented };

        using (var writer = new Utf8JsonWriter(stream, options))
        {
            using var document = JsonDocument.Parse(value);
            document.WriteTo(writer);
        }

        stream.Position = 0;

        using (var reader = new StreamReader(stream))
            return reader.ReadToEnd();
    }
}
```

### Proposal

```C#
namespace System.Text.Json
{
    partial class JsonDocument
    {
        public override string ToString() => ToString(indented: true);
        public string ToString(bool indented);
    }
}
```

### Usage

```C#
public static string ChangeIndentation(string value, bool indented)
{
    using var document = JsonDocument.Parse(value);
    return document.ToString(indented);
}
```

